# ===========================================
# Kvitt Mobile Environment
# Copy to .env and fill in your values.
# See docs/SETUP_KEYS.md for where to get each key.
# ===========================================

# Supabase Configuration
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-supabase-anon-key

# Backend API Configuration (production: kvitt.duckdns.org)
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://kvitt.duckdns.org/api
EXPO_PUBLIC_SOCKET_URL=https://kvitt.duckdns.org

# Expo Go — `npx expo start --tunnel` (ngrok)
# If you see: connect ECONNREFUSED 127.0.0.1:4040 — ngrok never started its local API.
# Fix (one-time): create a free ngrok account, then run:
#   npx ngrok config add-authtoken <token from https://dashboard.ngrok.com/get-started/your-authtoken>
# Also kill any stray ngrok.exe or other process using port 4040, then retry `npm run start:tunnel`.
#
# If you see: ngrok tunnel took too long to connect — the ngrok agent runs, but the cloud tunnel
# does not come up in time (often campus/corporate Wi‑Fi blocking or inspecting ngrok traffic).
# Try: `npm run start:tunnel:clear` (clears Metro cache), retry a few times, use phone hotspot,
# or run `npx ngrok diagnose` and ask IT to allow *.ngrok.com / *.ngrok-agent.com (see ngrok docs).
# Android without tunnel: USB debugging + `adb reverse tcp:8081 tcp:8081` then `npx expo start --localhost`.
